row.entry:
13.0-CURRENT after vop_symlink API change
	      (a_target is now
	      const.)

11-STABLE after several MFCs: updating &man.objcopy.1;
	      to properly handle little-endian MIPS64 object;
	      correcting mips64el test to use ELF header;
	      adding test for 64-bit ELF in _libelf_is_mips64el.

10-CURRENT after introduction of read capacity data
	      asynchronous notification in the &man.cam.4;
	      layer.

10-CURRENT after introduction of new &man.tcp.4;
	      socket options: TCP_KEEPINIT, TCP_KEEPIDLE,
	      TCP_KEEPINTVL, and TCP_KEEPCNT.

10-STABLE after merge of changes to &man.linux.4;
	      (rev 293477 through
	      293609 ).

10-STABLE after merge of changes to &man.figpar.3;
	      types/macros (rev
	      290275).

9.0-CURRENT after importing the &man.libprocstat.3;
	      library and &man.fuser.1; utility to the base
	      system.

9.0-STABLE after introduction of new &man.tcp.4;
	      socket options: TCP_KEEPINIT, TCP_KEEPIDLE,
	      TCP_KEEPINTVL, and TCP_KEEPCNT.

8.0-CURRENT after the introduction of LK_NODUP and
	      LK_NOWITNESS options in the &man.lockmgr.9;
	      space.

8.0-CURRENT after the introduction of the
	      &man.rw.try.rlock.9; and &man.rw.try.wlock.9;
	      functions.

7.0-CURRENT after the GNU &man.gzip.1;
	      implementation was replaced with a BSD licensed version
	      ported from NetBSD.

5.0-CURRENT after moving to XFree86 4 by default
	      for package builds, and after the new libc strnstr()
	      function was added.

5.2-CURRENT after changing &man.sema.timedwait.9;
	      to return 0 on success and a non-zero error code on
	      failure.
